      "id": "P_DRIVE_ISUP_METRIC_AS_A_VOLTAGE",
      "observable_contract": "Drive `isup_metric` as a voltage-coded supply-current estimate. The estimate must scale with the local supply ratio `V(vdd, vss) / vnom` clipped to the range `[0, 1.5]`. Normalize load as `V(load, vss) / vhi` clipped to `[0, 1]`. When the block is disabled or powered down, meaning `V(en) <= vth` or `V(pd) > vth`, drive `isup_metric = ipd * supply_scale`. Otherwise choose the active base metric as `iq1` when `V(mode) > vth` and `iq0` when `V(mode) <= vth`, then drive `isup_metric = (base_metric + load_gain * load_norm) * supply_scale`. The metric is not a real branch current; it is an observable behavioral macro-model output.",
      "required_signals": [
        "time",
        "en",
        "isup_metric",
        "load",
        "mode",
        "pd",
        "vdd",
        "vss"
